========================================================================
                 generica - a simple lisp-like language
         (c) 2009/2010 Christopher Bertels <bakkdoor@flasht.de>         
========================================================================

(goals)
  - implement a simple, yet powerful lisp-like language with:
    - a simple, yet useful object system
    - good concurrency semantics (via messaging, erlang style)
    - focus on immutability (but not purely functional like Haskell)
  - have fun implementing it
  - use ANSI C for the interpreter and possibly no external dependencies
  - small codebase and fast compilation, if possible

(contact)
  - contact me via my email adress shown above.

(more information coming soon)